<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06203011 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06203011 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  RAILROAD; INDIA  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  An runaway train sped through 33 stations before an illiterate herdsmantraveling in a cattle car crawled on the roofs of other rail cars to reach theengine and halt it, a news report said.;    Mohammad Anwar &quot;desperatelyfiddled with all the knobs and buttons (in the driver's cabin) and the trainfinally obeyed when he touched a green button at Karengi,&quot; the Press Trust ofIndia reported.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  MAN SCUTTLES OVER CARS TO STOP RUNAWAY TRAIN  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The incident occurred Friday after the engineer and his assistant stoppedat Matlabpur station and clambered down to check a broken pipe on the engine'sbody. Matlabpur is 125 miles east of New Delhi.;    Suddenly, the trainstarted moving and the two men watched helplessly as it gathered speed anddisappeared from sight, Press Trust said.;    Press Trust said an automaticswitching system allowed the train to travel 77 miles before Anwar halted it.;   Anwar, who was traveling with his animals in one of the wagons, reached theengine by crawling on the roofs of four cars.;    Press Trust did not say howAnwar realized the drivers were missing.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  New Delhi, India  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910721  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  July  </MONTH><PG.COL>  7A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  177  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday July 21, 199100203011,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>